# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: MagePath | Scene: MageInTheRuins2
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah bend her knees, crouching low towards the ground."
    new "Sarah bend her knees, crouching low towards the ground."

    old "Then, for a moment, held all of her magic energies into the muscles in her legs."
    new "Then, for a moment, held all of her magic energies into the muscles in her legs."

    old "When she released the energies, she less leapt than flew."
    new "When she released the energies, she less leapt than flew."

    old "Soaring through the air, she spun her body about, jumping easily over the horde of orcs."
    new "Soaring through the air, she spun her body about, jumping easily over the horde of orcs."

    old "Feeling the air rush along her body, Sarah felt herself descend back down to the ground."
    new "Feeling the air rush along her body, Sarah felt herself descend back down to the ground."

    old "Twisting one arm, she wielded her magics to pin herself in midair."
    new "Twisting one arm, she wielded her magics to pin herself in midair."

    old "Looking down, she saw the panicked expression on the faces of the goblins."
    new "Looking down, she saw the panicked expression on the faces of the goblins."

    old "Always lowly creatures, quick to fear, they were now besides themselves."
    new "Always lowly creatures, quick to fear, they were now besides themselves."

    old "As well they should be."
    new "As well they should be."

    old "Sarah extended her other arm and rained down fire on them."
    new "Sarah extended her other arm and rained down fire on them."

    old "They shrieked, high-pitched, like vermin when the fire consumed them."
    new "They shrieked, high-pitched, like vermin when the fire consumed them."

    old "Beyond their reach, and not yet having their blowguns readied, they could do nothing."
    new "Beyond their reach, and not yet having their blowguns readied, they could do nothing."

    old "Their poison, dangerous as it was, burned and evaporated into the air."
    new "Their poison, dangerous as it was, burned and evaporated into the air."

    old "Below her, Sarah could hear the orcs yelling."
    new "Below her, Sarah could hear the orcs yelling."

    old "Their strategy had been broken. They could do nothing to harm her now."
    new "Their strategy had been broken. They could do nothing to harm her now."

    old "She saw the orcs begin to retreat."
    new "She saw the orcs begin to retreat."

    old "But they were out of position, and from above them, she could easily burn more of them."
    new "But they were out of position, and from above them, she could easily burn more of them."

    old "Unlike the goblins, at least the orcs died with some dignity to them."
    new "Unlike the goblins, at least the orcs died with some dignity to them."

    old "Sarah extended her hand, pouring more fire down like lava."
    new "Sarah extended her hand, pouring more fire down like lava."

    old "She caught some orcs, a good number of them."
    new "She caught some orcs, a good number of them."

    old "But as they scattered, most of them managed to get beyond her reach."
    new "But as they scattered, most of them managed to get beyond her reach."

    old "For a moment, she thought of giving chase."
    new "For a moment, she thought of giving chase."

    old "They were more clever than she gave them credit for. They might have laid out traps, hoping that she would rush blindly after them."
    new "They were more clever than she gave them credit for. They might have laid out traps, hoping that she would rush blindly after them."

    old "Instead, Sarah released herself from the air and fell back down to the earth."
    new "Instead, Sarah released herself from the air and fell back down to the earth."

    old "Sarah looked around at the carnage."
    new "Sarah looked around at the carnage."

    old "Then, she quickly looked at Samayra."
    new "Then, she quickly looked at Samayra."

    old "She rushed over, instinctively."
    new "She rushed over, instinctively."

    old "She grabbed the girl."
    new "She grabbed the girl."

    old "Her eyes rushed across Samayra's body."
    new "Her eyes rushed across Samayra's body."

    old "Are you hurt? Tell me! Are you okay?!"
    new "Are you hurt? Tell me! Are you okay?!"

    old "Samayra pulled away."
    new "Samayra pulled away."

    old "Sarah, don't worry."
    new "Sarah, don't worry."

    old "She held out her arms. Flawless. Not even a bruise."
    new "She held out her arms. Flawless. Not even a bruise."

    old "I'm fine."
    new "I'm fine."

    old "One of them tried to grab me but...he paid for it."
    new "One of them tried to grab me but...he paid for it."

    old "Sarah laughed, finally letting go of the panic."
    new "Sarah laughed, finally letting go of the panic."

    old "Samayra was safe."
    new "Samayra was safe."

    old "It got pretty dangerous there towards the end."
    new "It got pretty dangerous there towards the end."

    old "But you...you did it!"
    new "But you...you did it!"

    old "Sarah saw that Samayra's eyes were wide, full of awe."
    new "Sarah saw that Samayra's eyes were wide, full of awe."

    old "Can I do that?"
    new "Can I do that?"

    old "Jump, the way you did! And then just...all that fire, and hanging in the air!"
    new "Jump, the way you did! And then just...all that fire, and hanging in the air!"

    old "Can you teach me?"
    new "Can you teach me?"

    old "Sure, but it's gonna be a while before you learn all of that."
    new "Sure, but it's gonna be a while before you learn all of that."

    old "For tonight, I think you should just try to get some sleep."
    new "For tonight, I think you should just try to get some sleep."

    old "Sleep?"
    new "Sleep?"

    old "After all that? I don't think I can..."
    new "After all that? I don't think I can..."

    old "You have to. Especially now."
    new "You have to. Especially now."

    old "We've scared them off, but Gods only know if they'll try something else."
    new "We've scared them off, but Gods only know if they'll try something else."

    old "We need to be ready."
    new "We need to be ready."

    old "Samayra sulked for a bit, only to nod and give in."
    new "Samayra sulked for a bit, only to nod and give in."

    old "Okay...but promise to wake me. I want to take a guard shift too."
    new "Okay...but promise to wake me. I want to take a guard shift too."

    old "Sure, just get some sleep and I'll promise I wake you."
    new "Sure, just get some sleep and I'll promise I wake you."

    old "With that, Sarah watched Samayra climb into her sleeping bag."
    new "With that, Sarah watched Samayra climb into her sleeping bag."

    old "Before long, the excitement had worn off, and the girl was fast asleep."
    new "Before long, the excitement had worn off, and the girl was fast asleep."

    old "Sarah smiled as she looked over Samayra."
    new "Sarah smiled as she looked over Samayra."

    old "She was safe."
    new "She was safe."

    old "Everywhere, burned flesh and ashes. Remnants of the orcs and goblins."
    new "Everywhere, burned flesh and ashes. Remnants of the orcs and goblins."

    old "Sarah couldn't feel too much pity for the creatures."
    new "Sarah couldn't feel too much pity for the creatures."

    old "Gods only knew what they would have done if she couldn't have stopped them."
    new "Gods only knew what they would have done if she couldn't have stopped them."

    old "Sarah spat on the ground."
    new "Sarah spat on the ground."

    old "She had given them a proper scare."
    new "She had given them a proper scare."

    old "They would warn the others that there was a girl in the ruins, not to be messed with."
    new "They would warn the others that there was a girl in the ruins, not to be messed with."

    old "At least...she hoped that was the case."
    new "At least...she hoped that was the case."

    old "She didn't want to keep testing her luck with orcs and goblins."
    new "She didn't want to keep testing her luck with orcs and goblins."

    old "Sarah sat down at the campfire."
    new "Sarah sat down at the campfire."

    old "She spun her wards about her, signals that would alert her, should anyone try to sneak up on her."
    new "She spun her wards about her, signals that would alert her, should anyone try to sneak up on her."

    old "Then, slowly, she allowed herself to fall asleep."
    new "Then, slowly, she allowed herself to fall asleep."

    old "Nervous. Anxious."
    new "Nervous. Anxious."

    old "Sarah woke early the next day."
    new "Sarah woke early the next day."

    old "Samayra had taken the last watch and was still awake."
    new "Samayra had taken the last watch and was still awake."

    old "The night had been cold."
    new "The night had been cold."

    old "But with even just the first rays of dawn, the air was already humid again."
    new "But with even just the first rays of dawn, the air was already humid again."

    old "She was eager to explore the city, less eager at the prospect of climbing the countless steps in this climate."
    new "She was eager to explore the city, less eager at the prospect of climbing the countless steps in this climate."

    old "She packed up camp and made towards one of the stairways that ascended up higher than any she'd ever seen."
    new "She packed up camp and made towards one of the stairways that ascended up higher than any she'd ever seen."

    old "Samayra, are you ready?"
    new "Samayra, are you ready?"

    old "She had packed up her things more quickly than Sarah had expected."
    new "She had packed up her things more quickly than Sarah had expected."

    old "Even with the orcs, she had kept her own. Sarah was starting to realize she might have underestimated the girl."
    new "Even with the orcs, she had kept her own. Sarah was starting to realize she might have underestimated the girl."

    old "Sarah started walking up the massive stairway."
    new "Sarah started walking up the massive stairway."

    old "Moss had overgrown most of it, yet the stone seemed resilient."
    new "Moss had overgrown most of it, yet the stone seemed resilient."

    old "It had been here for millenia. The fact that it had endured at all was impressive."
    new "It had been here for millenia. The fact that it had endured at all was impressive."

    old "Samayra was not far behind."
    new "Samayra was not far behind."

    old "Sarah had to turn around to look, just to make sure she was there. Samayra walked so lightly, her footsteps seemed to make no sounds."
    new "Sarah had to turn around to look, just to make sure she was there. Samayra walked so lightly, her footsteps seemed to make no sounds."

    old "As she went further up the stairway, the true size of the city was slowly coming into view."
    new "As she went further up the stairway, the true size of the city was slowly coming into view."

    old "With each step, she could look out further."
    new "With each step, she could look out further."

    old "First across the taller buildings, but soon after, even out across some of the trees."
    new "First across the taller buildings, but soon after, even out across some of the trees."

    old "The city, or what was left of it, seemed to stretch out for miles."
    new "The city, or what was left of it, seemed to stretch out for miles."

    old "It was hard to make out the exact size, given that so much of it was overgrown, but even from what little she saw, Sarah knew it was massive."
    new "It was hard to make out the exact size, given that so much of it was overgrown, but even from what little she saw, Sarah knew it was massive."

    old "Everything about the city made it obvious that it had once been home to many millions."
    new "Everything about the city made it obvious that it had once been home to many millions."

    old "Even Lethram, a large city in its own right, felt cramped and small compared to this place."
    new "Even Lethram, a large city in its own right, felt cramped and small compared to this place."

    old "Here, every street, stairway or plaza was massive. As if build to accomodate millions."
    new "Here, every street, stairway or plaza was massive. As if build to accomodate millions."

    old "Xan had told her the stories."
    new "Xan had told her the stories."

    old "The people who had lived here had been human, no different than her."
    new "The people who had lived here had been human, no different than her."

    old "And yet, they seemed too distant and alien from her. A people who did not dwell in tiny houses and hovels, but who drew up massive monuments."
    new "And yet, they seemed too distant and alien from her. A people who did not dwell in tiny houses and hovels, but who drew up massive monuments."

    old "And if Xan's stories were to be believed, walked among divinity."
    new "And if Xan's stories were to be believed, walked among divinity."

    old "One could walk down a street and simply encounter a God, performing miracles or dispensing ethereal truth."
    new "One could walk down a street and simply encounter a God, performing miracles or dispensing ethereal truth."

    old "Divinity, to these people, had been common."
    new "Divinity, to these people, had been common."

    old "As hollow as their world was now, so full had it once been."
    new "As hollow as their world was now, so full had it once been."

    old "But that was how people always were, Sarah thought to herself. One rarely reflects on the blessings of their own life, until those blessings are lost."
    new "But that was how people always were, Sarah thought to herself. One rarely reflects on the blessings of their own life, until those blessings are lost."

    old "She herself was no different."
    new "She herself was no different."

    old "Born a Princess, she had rarely ever wondered about just how fortunate her life had been."
    new "Born a Princess, she had rarely ever wondered about just how fortunate her life had been."

    old "Not until she lost it all."
    new "Not until she lost it all."

    old "And so she measured the value of all things, by their absence and her longing."
    new "And so she measured the value of all things, by their absence and her longing."

    old "Around her, the city changed as she ventured deeper."
    new "Around her, the city changed as she ventured deeper."

    old "Higher up on the plateaus, the design of the buildings seemed to become more intricate."
    new "Higher up on the plateaus, the design of the buildings seemed to become more intricate."

    old "She walked across a massive plaza, together with Samayra."
    new "She walked across a massive plaza, together with Samayra."

    old "She walked alone across a massive plaza."
    new "She walked alone across a massive plaza."

    old "Flanking the sides of the plaza were towering monuments, each very unique and distinct from any other building."
    new "Flanking the sides of the plaza were towering monuments, each very unique and distinct from any other building."

    old "A massive stone statue, marking and guarding the entrance."
    new "A massive stone statue, marking and guarding the entrance."

    old "Sarah looked at them for a while."
    new "Sarah looked at them for a while."

    old "Something about them was familiar."
    new "Something about them was familiar."

    old "Something about them felt as if she was seeing them not for the first time, but seeing them again. Recalling memories she never had."
    new "Something about them felt as if she was seeing them not for the first time, but seeing them again. Recalling memories she never had."

    old "One of the great statues was of a man, holding a spear with one hand, and holding back a wolf with the other."
    new "One of the great statues was of a man, holding a spear with one hand, and holding back a wolf with the other."

    old "The wolf was easily the size of the man itself, a massive beast."
    new "The wolf was easily the size of the man itself, a massive beast."

    old "Still, it heeded the hand of its master."
    new "Still, it heeded the hand of its master."

    old "Naelyon, The Huntsman."
    new "Naelyon, The Huntsman."

    old "Sarah had never been particularly pious in her life, nor given all too much thought to the Pantheon."
    new "Sarah had never been particularly pious in her life, nor given all too much thought to the Pantheon."

    old "Fables to be told to children to get them to behave."
    new "Fables to be told to children to get them to behave."

    old "But even fools knew the names of the greatest Gods of the Pantheon, and Naelyon ranked among them."
    new "But even fools knew the names of the greatest Gods of the Pantheon, and Naelyon ranked among them."

    old "God of the Hunt. The Forest. God of Beasts. God of the arrow."
    new "God of the Hunt. The Forest. God of Beasts. God of the arrow."

    old "Of him it was said that he could sit upon his throne in the heavens and strike down any soul he wished with his bow and arrow. Never missing."
    new "Of him it was said that he could sit upon his throne in the heavens and strike down any soul he wished with his bow and arrow. Never missing."

    old "Stories, Sarah told herself."
    new "Stories, Sarah told herself."

    old "But she had come to learn much of the world, and she wasn't quite so sure anymore."
    new "But she had come to learn much of the world, and she wasn't quite so sure anymore."

    old "And standing before the enormous statue that marked the entrance to the Huntsman's temple...she had never been in more doubt."
    new "And standing before the enormous statue that marked the entrance to the Huntsman's temple...she had never been in more doubt."

    old "All the other temples were equally marked by their respective God."
    new "All the other temples were equally marked by their respective God."

    old "But in this plaza, the largest of them all, was Naelyon."
    new "But in this plaza, the largest of them all, was Naelyon."

    old "Studying the stone constructs, Sarah realized that they were the only things in the city that had truly resisted any rot or decay."
    new "Studying the stone constructs, Sarah realized that they were the only things in the city that had truly resisted any rot or decay."

    old "The statues were the only objects that had suffered not even the smallest of damage to their surface."
    new "The statues were the only objects that had suffered not even the smallest of damage to their surface."

    old "Even the plants seemed to pull away from them, leaving the statues mostly untouched by nature."
    new "Even the plants seemed to pull away from them, leaving the statues mostly untouched by nature."

    old "Repulsing nature from themselves."
    new "Repulsing nature from themselves."

    old "Did that mark them divine or mark them wicked?"
    new "Did that mark them divine or mark them wicked?"

    old "She shuddered. She didn't want to be spend too much time staying still."
    new "She shuddered. She didn't want to be spend too much time staying still."

    old "Memories of the Orc attack from the night before still haunted her."
    new "Memories of the Orc attack from the night before still haunted her."

    old "It had been dangerous. One slip up and who knows what might have happened."
    new "It had been dangerous. One slip up and who knows what might have happened."

    old "And she was far from safe."
    new "And she was far from safe."

    old "Who knew how many vile creatures made their home in this place."
    new "Who knew how many vile creatures made their home in this place."

    old "It would be better to keep moving."
    new "It would be better to keep moving."

    old "With the sun overhead, she walked further along the plaza, up towards a large archway."
    new "With the sun overhead, she walked further along the plaza, up towards a large archway."

    old "It seemed to mark the entrance into a new part of the city."
    new "It seemed to mark the entrance into a new part of the city."

    old "More markings. Symbols. Statues."
    new "More markings. Symbols. Statues."

    old "Was she getting closer to the heart of the city?"
    new "Was she getting closer to the heart of the city?"

    old "Xan had shown her a map once, a long time ago."
    new "Xan had shown her a map once, a long time ago."

    old "The shape of the city itself was circular, with all the great roads leading towards the same place."
    new "The shape of the city itself was circular, with all the great roads leading towards the same place."

    old "The Imperial Palace."
    new "The Imperial Palace."

    old "Home of the Empress that had hollowed her world."
    new "Home of the Empress that had hollowed her world."

    old "Once, it had been the center of all of the human race."
    new "Once, it had been the center of all of the human race."

    old "Now, a forgotten ruin. Lost to the jungle."
    new "Now, a forgotten ruin. Lost to the jungle."

    old "Sarah kept her eyes out as she kept to the main road."
    new "Sarah kept her eyes out as she kept to the main road."

    old "She saw no hints of orcs or goblins."
    new "She saw no hints of orcs or goblins."

    old "Then again, she hadn't spotted them the last time until it was too late either."
    new "Then again, she hadn't spotted them the last time until it was too late either."

    old "All she could hope for was enough distance so that they could not jump her."
    new "All she could hope for was enough distance so that they could not jump her."

    old "If she had space to use her magic, she had the advantage."
    new "If she had space to use her magic, she had the advantage."

    old "How old do you think this place is?"
    new "How old do you think this place is?"

    old "Sarah looked at Samayra as they kept walking."
    new "Sarah looked at Samayra as they kept walking."

    old "Several millenia, at least. That's if Xan was to be believed."
    new "Several millenia, at least. That's if Xan was to be believed."

    old "Samayra's eyes went wide."
    new "Samayra's eyes went wide."

    old "Wow...I thought Bagrad was old..."
    new "Wow...I thought Bagrad was old..."

    old "Bagrad had been old and ancient compared to most places of the world."
    new "Bagrad had been old and ancient compared to most places of the world."

    old "But this place alone, stood apart."
    new "But this place alone, stood apart."

    old "They had a whole civilization here...long before any other came along."
    new "They had a whole civilization here...long before any other came along."

    old "Samayra's eyes scanned every part of the city."
    new "Samayra's eyes scanned every part of the city."

    old "I wish I could have seen it..."
    new "I wish I could have seen it..."

    old "She wished for the same."
    new "She wished for the same."

    old "You ever felt the same about Bagrad?"
    new "You ever felt the same about Bagrad?"

    old "Samayra suddenly looked down at the ground. Her shoulders fell."
    new "Samayra suddenly looked down at the ground. Her shoulders fell."

    old "Even when I was born it was a shadow of what it had been."
    new "Even when I was born it was a shadow of what it had been."

    old "But some parts of it were still as they had been in the glory days."
    new "But some parts of it were still as they had been in the glory days."

    old "Like the gardens."
    new "Like the gardens."

    old "Sarah nodded. Those had been beautiful."
    new "Sarah nodded. Those had been beautiful."

    old "Gods, it felt so long ago."
    new "Gods, it felt so long ago."

    old "My dad would always tell me the stories...but I think even when he was born the city had faded."
    new "My dad would always tell me the stories...but I think even when he was born the city had faded."

    old "So it was always like he was just telling me stories."
    new "So it was always like he was just telling me stories."

    old "But they weren't real stories. Nothing he had experienced for himself."
    new "But they weren't real stories. Nothing he had experienced for himself."

    old "He was just telling me stuff he had read in his own books. Heard from his own father."
    new "He was just telling me stuff he had read in his own books. Heard from his own father."

    old "Samayra paused."
    new "Samayra paused."

    old "I think it always felt strange...to be the heir to something you never really wanted."
    new "I think it always felt strange...to be the heir to something you never really wanted."

    old "I think I can relate. A little."
    new "I think I can relate. A little."

    old "The two walked along in silence for a while."
    new "The two walked along in silence for a while."

    old "At first, the great road that carried them towards the heart of the city had seemed not so long."
    new "At first, the great road that carried them towards the heart of the city had seemed not so long."

    old "Staring down the road, Sarah was sure she could make out the shapes of the Imperial Palace."
    new "Staring down the road, Sarah was sure she could make out the shapes of the Imperial Palace."

    old "But this, she soon learned, was little more than an optical illusion."
    new "But this, she soon learned, was little more than an optical illusion."

    old "With everything as vast and enormous as it was, it made all things appear normal in size."
    new "With everything as vast and enormous as it was, it made all things appear normal in size."

    old "And so as they spend most of the day walking, Sarah soon realized they would not make it to the Imperial Palace before nightfall."
    new "And so as they spend most of the day walking, Sarah soon realized they would not make it to the Imperial Palace before nightfall."

    old "She contemplated."
    new "She contemplated."

    old "Pressing on would be dangerous."
    new "Pressing on would be dangerous."

    old "Even if they made it to the Imperial Palace, it would be dark."
    new "Even if they made it to the Imperial Palace, it would be dark."

    old "That place was no doubt dangerous. Going in at dark was not something she was planning for."
    new "That place was no doubt dangerous. Going in at dark was not something she was planning for."

    old "They'd have to camp out, no matter way. Wait for next morning."
    new "They'd have to camp out, no matter way. Wait for next morning."

    old "I think it's best if we make camp for now."
    new "I think it's best if we make camp for now."

    old "Really? You don't wanna press on? I promise I can keep walking!"
    new "Really? You don't wanna press on? I promise I can keep walking!"

    old "I know you can, but I want to reach the Imperial Palace with some sun left. Not come upon it at night."
    new "I know you can, but I want to reach the Imperial Palace with some sun left. Not come upon it at night."

    old "I don't know what we'll find in there."
    new "I don't know what we'll find in there."

    old "But you do feel it...don't you?"
    new "But you do feel it...don't you?"

    old "The pulsing beat that seemed to emanate from the heart of the city."
    new "The pulsing beat that seemed to emanate from the heart of the city."

    old "A rhythmic wave of energy that ran across her skin."
    new "A rhythmic wave of energy that ran across her skin."

    old "Something. But she could not tell what."
    new "Something. But she could not tell what."

    old "Just set up camp for now."
    new "Just set up camp for now."

    old "I'll start setting up some magical wards, make sure we're not surprised again."
    new "I'll start setting up some magical wards, make sure we're not surprised again."

    old "Samayra nodded and began to set up camp."
    new "Samayra nodded and began to set up camp."

    old "Sarah, in turn, began to weave her magical wards and barriers."
    new "Sarah, in turn, began to weave her magical wards and barriers."

    old "Some to trigger a warning alert. Others, traps that would burst into flame. Some to block arrows and other attacks."
    new "Some to trigger a warning alert. Others, traps that would burst into flame. Some to block arrows and other attacks."

    old "Magic was nothing if not useful."
    new "Magic was nothing if not useful."

    old "And Sarah was determined not to be taken by surprise again."
    new "And Sarah was determined not to be taken by surprise again."

    old "She started setting up camp."
    new "She started setting up camp."

    old "First she finished making her bed, a small campfire."
    new "First she finished making her bed, a small campfire."

    old "After that, she began to weave her spells."
    new "After that, she began to weave her spells."

    old "Magical wards and barriers, surrounding her campsite."
    new "Magical wards and barriers, surrounding her campsite."

    old "Having finished conjuring her defenses, Sarah sat down near the campfire."
    new "Having finished conjuring her defenses, Sarah sat down near the campfire."

    old "Sarah looked over at Samayra, who had already crawled into her sleeping bag."
    new "Sarah looked over at Samayra, who had already crawled into her sleeping bag."

    old "The girl was frail as it was, she needed all the warmth she could get."
    new "The girl was frail as it was, she needed all the warmth she could get."

    old "Still, she saw Samayra twisting and turning about."
    new "Still, she saw Samayra twisting and turning about."

    old "Samayra, you need to get some sleep."
    new "Samayra, you need to get some sleep."

    old "She heard Samayra loudly puffing, like a scolded child that didn't agree."
